items.title: Awesome Python Data Science
items.content_text: ### Machine Learning / General Purpose Machine Learning * [dlib (⭐14k)](https://github.com/davisking/dlib) - Toolkit for making real-world machine learning and data analysis applications in C++ (Python bindings). ### Machine Learning / Ensemble Methods * [Stacking (⭐224)](https://github.com/ikki407/stacking) - Simple and useful stacking library written in Python. ### Machine Learning / Imbalanced Datasets * [imbalanced-learn (⭐7k)](https://github.com/scikit-learn-contrib/imbalanced-learn) - Module to perform under-sampling and over-sampling with various techniques. ### Deep Learning / PyTorch * [skorch (⭐6.1k)](https://github.com/dnouri/skorch) - A scikit-learn compatible neural network library that wraps PyTorch. * [ChemicalX (⭐745)](https://github.com/AstraZeneca/chemicalx) - A PyTorch-based deep learning library for drug pair scoring. ### Deep Learning / TensorFlow * [tfdeploy (⭐354)](https://github.com/riga/tfdeploy) - Deploy TensorFlow graphs for fast evaluation and export to TensorFlow-less environments running numpy. * [Ludwig (⭐12k)](https://github.com/uber/ludwig) - A toolbox that allows one to train and test deep learning models without the need to write code. * [Hyperas (⭐2.2k)](https://github.com/maxpumperla/hyperas) - Keras + Hyperopt: A straightforward wrapper for a convenient hyperparameter. ### Model Explanation / Others * [dalex (⭐1.4k)](https://github.com/ModelOriented/DALEX) - moDel Agnostic Language for Exploration and explanation. * [Shapley (⭐220)](https://github.com/benedekrozemberczki/shapley) - A data-driven framework to quantify the value of classifiers in a machine learning ensemble. * [tensorboard-pytorch (⭐8k)](https://github.com/lanpa/tensorboard-pytorch) - Tensorboard for PyTorch (and chainer, mxnet, numpy, ...). ### Optimization / Others * [sklearn-genetic-opt (⭐343)](https://github.com/rodrigo-arenas/Sklearn-genetic-opt) - Hyperparameters tuning and feature selection using evolutionary algorithms. * [OR-Tools](https://developers.google.com/optimization) - An open-source software suite for optimization by Google; provides a unified programming interface to a half dozen solvers: SCIP, GLPK, GLOP, CP-SAT, CPLEX, and Gurobi. ### Experimentation / Synthetic Data * [Neptune](https://neptune.ai) - A lightweight ML experiment tracking, results visualization, and management tool. * [Sacred (⭐4.3k)](https://github.com/IDSIA/sacred) - A tool to help you configure, organize, log, and reproduce experiments. ### Data Validation / Synthetic Data * [pandera (⭐3.9k)](https://github.com/unionai-oss/pandera) - A lightweight, flexible, and expressive statistical data testing library. ### Evaluation / Synthetic Data * [sklearn-evaluation (⭐3)](https://github.com/edublancas/sklearn-evaluation) - Model evaluation made easy: plots, tables, and markdown reports. * [AI Fairness 360 (⭐2.6k)](https://github.com/IBM/AIF360) - Fairness metrics for datasets and ML models, explanations, and algorithms to mitigate bias in datasets and models. ### Quantum Computing / Synthetic Data * [cirq (⭐4.6k)](https://github.com/quantumlib/Cirq) - A python framework for creating, editing, and invoking Noisy Intermediate Scale Quantum (NISQ) circuits. ### Conversion / Synthetic Data * [sklearn-porter (⭐1.3k)](https://github.com/nok/sklearn-porter) - Transpile trained scikit-learn estimators to C, Java, JavaScript, and others.
items.content_html:
Machine Learning / General Purpose Machine Learning

  • dlib (⭐14k) - Toolkit for making real-world machine learning and data analysis applications in C++ (Python bindings).

Machine Learning / Ensemble Methods

  • Stacking (⭐224) - Simple and useful stacking library written in Python.

Machine Learning / Imbalanced Datasets

  • imbalanced-learn (⭐7k) - Module to perform under-sampling and over-sampling with various techniques.

Deep Learning / PyTorch

  • skorch (⭐6.1k) - A scikit-learn compatible neural network library that wraps PyTorch.
  • ChemicalX (⭐745) - A PyTorch-based deep learning library for drug pair scoring.

Deep Learning / TensorFlow

  • tfdeploy (⭐354) - Deploy TensorFlow graphs for fast evaluation and export to TensorFlow-less environments running numpy.
  • Ludwig (⭐12k) - A toolbox that allows one to train and test deep learning models without the need to write code.
  • Hyperas (⭐2.2k) - Keras + Hyperopt: A straightforward wrapper for a convenient hyperparameter.

Model Explanation / Others

  • dalex (⭐1.4k) - moDel Agnostic Language for Exploration and explanation.
  • Shapley (⭐220) - A data-driven framework to quantify the value of classifiers in a machine learning ensemble.
  • tensorboard-pytorch (⭐8k) - Tensorboard for PyTorch (and chainer, mxnet, numpy, ...).

Optimization / Others

  • sklearn-genetic-opt (⭐343) - Hyperparameters tuning and feature selection using evolutionary algorithms.
  • OR-Tools - An open-source software suite for optimization by Google; provides a unified programming interface to a half dozen solvers: SCIP, GLPK, GLOP, CP-SAT, CPLEX, and Gurobi.

Experimentation / Synthetic Data

  • Neptune - A lightweight ML experiment tracking, results visualization, and management tool.
  • Sacred (⭐4.3k) - A tool to help you configure, organize, log, and reproduce experiments.

Data Validation / Synthetic Data

  • pandera (⭐3.9k) - A lightweight, flexible, and expressive statistical data testing library.

Evaluation / Synthetic Data

  • sklearn-evaluation (⭐3) - Model evaluation made easy: plots, tables, and markdown reports.
  • AI Fairness 360 (⭐2.6k) - Fairness metrics for datasets and ML models, explanations, and algorithms to mitigate bias in datasets and models.

Quantum Computing / Synthetic Data

  • cirq (⭐4.6k) - A python framework for creating, editing, and invoking Noisy Intermediate Scale Quantum (NISQ) circuits.

Conversion / Synthetic Data

  • sklearn-porter (⭐1.3k) - Transpile trained scikit-learn estimators to C, Java, JavaScript, and others.

items.content_text:
### Assembly / Tools

*   **[Minimap2 (⭐2k)](https://github.com/lh3/minimap2)** - Minimap2 is an pairwise aligner for genomic and spliced nucleotide sequences. It can perform the assembly-to-assembly alignment, and works with gzip'd FASTQ, FASTA formats. It also finds overlaps between long-reads.
*   **[D-GENIES](https://dgenies.toulouse.inra.fr/)** - **D**ot plot large **Gen**omes in an **I**nteractive, **E**fficient and **S**imple way. It is an online tool designed to support large genome, compare two genomes, and you can interact with the dot plot to improve the visualisation. It can also be used for extension of minimap2 by uploading the output generated in PAF(Pairwise mApping Format) or MAF(Multiple Alignment File) alignment files to D-GENIES

items.title: Awesome Qubes OS
items.content_text:
### System Information & Requirements

*   [Certified Hardware](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/certified-hardware/) - We aim for these vendors to be as diverse as possible in terms of geography, cost, and availability.
*   [Hardware compatibility list (HCL)](https://www.qubes-os.org/hcl/) - The HCL is a compilation of reports generated and submitted by users across various Qubes versions about their hardware’s compatibility with Qubes.

### How-to guides

*   [How to back up, restore, and migrate](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/how-to-back-up-restore-and-migrate/) - With Qubes, it’s easy and secure to back up and restore your whole system, as well as to migrate between two physical machines.
*   [How to copy and paste text](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/how-to-copy-and-paste-text/) - This page is about copying and pasting plain text.
*   [How to copy from dom0](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/how-to-copy-from-dom0/) - This page covers copying files and clipboard text between dom0 and domUs.
*   [How to install software](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/how-to-install-software/) - When you wish to install software in Qubes OS, you should generally install it in a template.
*   [How to use PCI devices](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/how-to-use-pci-devices/) - Unlike other devices (USB, block, mic), PCI devices need to be attached on VM-bootup.
*   [How to use devices](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/how-to-use-devices/) - This is an overview of device handling in Qubes OS.
*   [How to use optical discs](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/how-to-use-optical-discs/) - Passthrough reading and recording (a.k.a., “burning”) are not supported by Qubes OS.

### Templates

*   [Debian templates](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/templates/debian/) - The Debian template is an officially supported template in Qubes OS.
*   [Minimal templates](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/templates/minimal/) - The minimal templates are lightweight versions of their standard template counterparts.
*   [Templates](https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/templates/) - In Getting Started, we covered the distinction in Qubes OS between where you install your software and where you run your software.

### VM-Hardening

*   [Kicksecure](https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/Kicksecure-Qubes_Security) - The following list of actionable items can help to improve security on the Qubes platform, and by extension Kicksecure ™ for Qubes users.
*   [Qcrypt (⭐18)](https://github.com/3hhh/qcrypt) -qcrypt is a multilayer encryption tool for Qubes OS.
